1.00	Pacific_Coast_Baptist_Bible_College	Heartland Baptist Bible College	Heartland Baptist Bible College is an unaccredited Independent Fundamental Baptist Bible college in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, which offers undergraduate diplomas (HBBC is not allowed by the state of Oklahoma to issue degrees) in pastoral theology, missions, youth, Christian ministries, music education, Christian education (elementary and secondary), and secretarial science. Sam Davison, the current president of the institution, retired as pastor of Southwest Baptist Church, Oklahoma City, in May, 2010. Prior to 1998, the school was located in San Dimas, California and was known as Pacific Coast Baptist Bible College.	
